# 1.Population Census

-- Problem

Find the total population of all cities where the continent is Asia.

--Tables Used

CITY

COUNTRY

-- Task Summary

Join CITY and COUNTRY tables using CountryCode

Filter records where Continent = 'Asia'

Calculate the sum of population


-- SQL Solution

SELECT SUM(CITY.POPULATION) AS SUM_OF_POPULATIONS
FROM CITY 
LEFT JOIN COUNTRY
ON CITY.CountryCode = COUNTRY.Code
WHERE CONTINENT = "Asia";
============================================================================

# 2.African Cities

--Problem

List the names of all cities located in countries where the continent is Africa.

-- Tables Used

CITY

COUNTRY


--Task Summary

Join city and country tables

Filter by Continent = 'Africa'

Display only city names


--SQL Solution

SELECT CITY.NAME 
FROM CITY
LEFT JOIN COUNTRY
ON CITY.CountryCode = COUNTRY.Code
WHERE CONTINENT = "Africa";
====================================================================================

# 3.Average Population of Each Continent

--Problem

Calculate the average population of cities for each continent, rounded down to the nearest integer.


--Tables Used

CITY

COUNTRY


-- Task Summary

Join tables using country codes

Group data by continent

Use AVG() aggregation function

Apply FLOOR() to remove decimals


-- SQL Solution

SELECT COUNTRY.Continent,FLOOR(AVG(CITY.Population))
FROM CITY
INNER  JOIN COUNTRY
ON CITY.CountryCode = COUNTRY.Code
GROUP BY COUNTRY.Continent;
===========================================================================================================

# 4.The Report

--Problem
Generate a report showing:

Student name

Grade

Marks

Students with grade ≥ 8 should display names.
Students with grade < 8 should display NULL instead of names.
Results must be ordered by grade (descending) and name (ascending).


-- Tables Used

Students

Grades


--Task Summary


Join students and grades based on marks range


Use conditional logic to show or hide names


Apply multiple sorting conditions


-- SQL Solution
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN g.grade >= 8 THEN s.name
        ELSE NULL
    END AS name,
    g.grade,
    s.marks
FROM students s
JOIN grades g
ON s.marks BETWEEN g.min_mark AND g.max_mark
ORDER BY g.grade DESC, name ASC;



